# artifactgraph

MCP: [raintr91/artifactgraph](https://github.com/raintr91/artifactgraph) · `/artifactgraph` · [ARTIFACTGRAPH](docs/operational/ARTIFACTGRAPH.md) · [INTERNALS](docs/operational/ARTIFACTGRAPH-INTERNALS.md)

## Prefer local MCP (like CodeGraph prefers explore)

On artifact skills (`/spec`, `/legacy-spec`, `/dev-grill-docs`, `/grill-with-docs`, `/prototype`, `/grill-prototype`, `/unit`, `/test`, `/platform-mark`):

1. **`artifactgraph_analyze` / `grill_check` / `gaps` / `parity_check` first** — before dumping registries or inventing shell gen.
2. **Grill + parity-drift questions are local** — common vs feature-only, confirm blocks, create≠edit / label / empty A/B/C. Ask the **member**.  
   **context-orphan** = warn only (data action ≠ data màn); **không** ép A/B/C.
3. **Gen** via `artifactgraph_gen` allowlist when `artifactgraph.json` exists (`genDry`, `gen`, `unitGen`, …).
4. Cloud only **`cloudPromptSlice`**: missing Mo* slots, unknown legacy symbols (+ **`parityFindings` schema same turn**), unknown patterns — never full `registries/` or `codegen/templates/`.
5. After implement → registry promote + `artifactgraph_remember` (`kind=grill|parity`).
